And so, this right over,
we saw from the beginning,

00:08:00.845 --> 00:08:02.762
this is the slope of L.

00:08:04.711 --> 00:08:05.961
So, slope of L.

00:08:09.273 --> 00:08:13.071
And how does this relate
to the slope of M?

00:08:13.071 --> 00:08:15.319
Notice, the slope of M is
the negative reciprocal

00:08:15.319 --> 00:08:16.267
of this.

00:08:16.267 --> 00:08:18.451
You take the reciprocal,
you're going to get DE over AD,

00:08:18.451 --> 00:08:20.721
and then you have to take
this negative right over here.

00:08:20.721 --> 00:08:23.287
So, we could write this
as the negative reciprocal

00:08:23.287 --> 00:08:24.454
of slope of M.

00:08:26.548 --> 00:08:29.298
Negative reciprocal of M's slope.

00:08:36.885 --> 00:08:37.989
And there you have it.

00:08:37.989 --> 00:08:39.743
We've just shown that if we

00:08:39.743 --> 00:08:42.493
assume L and M are perpendicular,

00:08:43.437 --> 00:08:45.508
and we setup these similar triangles,

00:08:45.508 --> 00:08:47.427
and we're able to show,

00:08:47.427 --> 00:08:50.817
that the slope of L is
the negative reciprocal

00:08:50.817 --> 00:08:52.317
of the slope of M.

